'''''Star Wars: The Official Magazine'' 7''' was the 7th issue of the ''[[Star Wars: The Official Magazine]]'', covering [[April]] and [[May]] [[1997]] and containing 66 pages.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*[[Feel the Force]]
*[[Second Trooper]]: [[Shelagh Fraser|To Live and Die on Tatooine]] {{C|by [[Dave Bassom|David Bassom]]}}
*[[Jawa's Corner|Jawas' Corner]]

===Features===
*"[[The Legend Renewed]]" {{C|by [[Jim Swallow]]}}
*:<small>We meet the [[Industrial Light & Magic]] team who created the Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition.</small>
*"[[The Making of Star Wars (feature)|The Making of ''Star Wars'']]: I've Got a Bad Feeling About This..." {{C|by [[Dan Abnett]]}}
*:<small>As [[George Lucas]] and [[Gary Kurtz]] stretch the boundaries of filmmaking, the atmosphere gets strained&hellip;</small>
*"[[Star Wars at Elstree|''Star Wars'' at Elstree]]" {{C|by [[Paul Welsh]]}}
*:<small>[[Paul Welsh]] remembers Lucasfilm's special association with the facility where the Star Wars and [[Wikipedia:Indiana Jones]] films were produced.</small>
*"[[Nuts and Bolts]]" {{C|by [[Marcus Hearn]]}}
*:<small>[[Nick Harrison]] describes working on the Star Wars trilogy as part of Elstree Studios' engineering workshop.</small>
*"[[The Star Wars Stooges|The ''Star Wars'' Stooges]]" {{C|by [[Iain Lowson]]}}
*:<small>[[Peter Diamond]] reveals how he and his team choreographed some of Star Wars' most dangerous sequences.</small>
*[[Anthony Daniels' Set Diary]]: A Touch of the Suns
*:<small>[[Anthony Daniels]] continues his exclusive memoirs.</small>
*"Missing in Action" {{C|by Iain Lowson}}
*:<small>The Star Wars Special Edition restores much missing material to the regenerated print &ndash; but what of the footage that stayed on the cutting room floor?</small>
*[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species (real-world book)|''The Essential Guide to Alien Species'']]: The [[Hutt/Legends|Hutts]]
*:<small>A detailed look at the most infamous species in the Star Wars universe.</small>
*"[[Shadow Stalker]]" Part 1
*:<small>[[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] rogue [[Wrenga Jixton|Jix]] is late for a very dangerous rendezvous&hellip;</small>

